I think you got that backward. Rarely does any industry every choose obsolesces or bankruptcy for the same of pushing an agenda. When that didn't work they would normally have needed to change tracks, but as the movie and TV deals became more and more lucrative, they didn't really need to. They could just continue as they were and still survive. They're operating without a safety net right now
